rComments: Lectures were insightful & thorough & he used slides, literature & videos to convey info in depth. He answered whatever questions I had & encouraged students to speak & share their experiences in class. He checked in to  ensure that he wasn't going too fast & slowed down if we were confused. Exams = take home essay questions. MUST do all readings.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: I enjoyed his lectures+ structure, and the material was interesting. You have 3 big assignments that consist of lots of writing but aren't hard. Teacher is nice but distant. He doesn't read the chat or post the notes on Brightspace. His lectures aren't too long, and they're recorded. You can teach yourself the material; lots of texts+ documentaries

This course is AMAZING! He's very passionate about this course, which made it extremely interesting! He answered all our questions and even asked students to talk about their own experiences. He also gave us lots of freedom with our take home exams. We had 1-2 weeks to do the exams, which was nice. Only downside is that he wouldn't post his slides.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: For the final assignment worth 50%, he refused to give a page count. Students begged to get an idea of what he expected and he said average 10 pages per questions with 2 questions. He gave the prompt 12 days before the assignment was due meaning to meet his expectations you'd have to write a page a day not including research and editing.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: terrible prof..... he is very very rude and also he cannot teach. thankfully the TA was nice but the prof accused me of fraud and plagiarism.... with no proof.... and when i emailed him to "talk" about it he ignored me. very unprofessional prof, very childish. his material is a lot of work and gives a lottttt of readings.

Gives terribly subjective grades and very unclear instruction, he doesn't give explanations or commentaries even if you ask him. He knows what he's talking about but is disorganized so it can get you lost. He is also impolite and blames his students for not understanding instead of clarifying. You can have a good grade if he likes you, you decide.
Note à l'instinct, de mauvaise foie. Je ne recommande pas ce prof, il ne fait pas d'effort pour faire comprendre ses élève, et note comme bon lui semble.

Le cours est intéressant et généralement bien organisé. Le prof est perdu lorsquil sagit de bien expliquer ce quil attend de ses étudiants. Le cours a eu lieu sur Zoom et lorsque son internet ne fonctionnait pas, il a blâmé ses étudiants. Il ne change pas les notes et il note ses examens par le nombre de mots et nombre de mots et non la qualité.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Professeur très passionnè
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Cours au choix de génie, pas de travail intellectuel pendant la session. Pas besoin d'assister aux cours (sauf infos sur examens) pour passer. Les topics sont intéressants. Par contre, être prêt à lire pas mal d'articles postés en ligne pour les résumés. Et des dissertations en examens. Je conseille de commencer les résumés le plus tôt possible.

I would never recommend taking this prof to anyone, he has no will to help his students. He was very unwilling to repeat himself or clarify things that may not have been well explained. He goes on and on in class talking AT the students, never incites any of us to speak or participate. He never posts any of his content online.

god, this course was a true PAIN. very long readings with summaries due at the end of the sem. NO clear instructions posted for any evaluations. gets annoyed by questions asked re: instructions citing that he already talked about it. has a master powerpoint which is NOT posted online - you have to go to class! but easy A if you don't overthink it!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Terrible, terrible, terrible. Run while you still can. The guy won't give any instructions for assignments, won't upload anything (powerpoints, evaluation grids), always goes off-topic so you don't learn anything, and is very rude and inconsiderate when you ask him questions. Worst prof i've ever had. Don't take a class with him, you will regret it
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Absolutely horrible prof. Doesn't care to help his students and is very rude when they ask questions. Goes off-topic way too much to the point where we learn nothing we're supposed to. Avoid him if possible

Malgré qu'il est passioné de la religion, il n'est pas très bon à l'enseigner. Il fait rien que lire ses slides de Powerpoint. Son "enseignement" est assigner 40-50 pages de lecture + un documentaire de 50 minute par semaine, et écrire un résumé pour chaque (25% de la note). Particulièrement insulté par des simples questions de la part des étudiant

While he definitely knows what he's talking about, he is very unacessible and gets salty when students ask him questions. He goes over the material really fast during lectures, and he doesn't upload anything, really NOTHING, like he's allergic to it (no powerpoints, no instructions for papers, no evaluation grids), really unhelpful
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: He is awful. Doesn't post the powerpoints online, so attendance is mandatory and they are also very scattered with little information. On top of class, you have to read and watch videos and write resumes on them (twice per week). His classes are very dull and he goes a bit too fast. The only good thing is that he posts the exam question beforehand.

J'ai beaucoup apprécié mon cours SRS1512 avec Mr Gardaz. C'est un professeur passionné ! Il met ses compétences au profit de ces élèves. Qui plus est, il donne les questions du midterm et de l'examen final une semaine à l'avance, ce qui est appréciable.

I enjoyed the class cause i'm personally interested in the subject but MAN OH MAN was that class an adventure. Make sure you think about your question 10 times before you ask it cause he will call you out if it's not relevant. All in all, it wasnt hard at all to get a decent grade since the questions for the midterm and exam were given before.

he teaches an hour/an hour and a half of class and then would make us watch videos which was especially insulting considering he asked us to read all our readings (sometimes up to 60 pages), finish them 3 weeks before the material was taught and make a summary out of it. i never get overwhelmed, but this class made me lose it. never again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I took Mr. Gardaz' class "Religion du monde" for Fall 2019, and loved it ! He definitely knows what he's talking about, and has travelled enough to share personal experience. There are lectures to be made every week, and you are required to make a resumé of each one of them, but the texts are quite easy, and not so long. Amazing prof.

He expects resumes of weekly readings (20-30 pages of heavy material) to be handed in at the end of term. Powerpoint is ONE big document so you can't really navigate it. He seems interested but he isn't very good at captivating interest (i.e. doing the same thing over and over again, twice a week, gets very old).

Prof is rude. Il demande la participation des étudiants mais te fait sentir stupide si ta réponse n'est pas celle qu'il attend. Il prend les présences, si tu manques 5 cours il ne te laisse pas faire l'examen final. Très difficile de comprendre comment il note les travaux et de le consulter à ce sujet. He doesn't care.
La seule et unique raison pour prendre ce cours est simple: il donne les questions des examens à l'avance.
Très charismatique, rend la matière du cours intéressante.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Hilarious', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Lectures are long - nothing but reading off a PowerPoint and showing YouTube videos. Readings are long and heavy. Only 3 evaluations: 25% midterm, 25% chapter summaries, and 50% final exam. Make sure your answers are long, as he likes length.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: M. Gardaz ne met pas ses PowerPoints en ligne donc il est important de se rendre en classe. Pas tout le temps facile à suivre car il présente beaucoup d'info disparate et fait beaucoup d'aller-retour. Mais il donne les questions d'examen à l'avance et elles ne sont pas difficiles. Il comprends que les étudiants sont occupés. Cours intéressant.

His lectures tend to be dry, but he seems to know his stuff. Get ready to read because whatever loose leaf you're getting, you're reading all of it. No notes on brightspace so attend class. He made us make a summary of readings. but grades fairly easy. Gives exam questions in advance and makes it general so you can do some extra research on it.

Son cours est facile. Il donne les questions d'examen à l'avance, mais il les donne au hasard dans ses cours : il faut donc être présent. Ses examens sont faciles et ses cours sont clairs. Il a beaucoup de difficulté avec la technologie et il est impatient, mais son cours est tellement facile que ça vaut la peine de le prendre.

Un des meilleurs professeurs de ma scolarité. Professeur Gardaz connait parfaitement la matière qu'il enseigne et la transmet avec passion. Il est aussi très ouvert au discours et aide avec plaisir les élèves en cas de problème. Il y a beaucoup de lectures à faire, mais quand on est passionné par le cours, on ne compte pas les pages!
This teacher speaks purely to listen to himself. No possibility to have any sort of exchange with him. If you don't believe what he does, just smile and nod. Criticism too strong to be educational.

It absolutely baffles me how a "professor" who is so incompetent, biased, and unprofessional has managed to progress so far up the academic ladder. He appears to be completely clueless about his own subject material. At one point, he called one of the people in the class an "intellectual terrorist" for believing in the social sciences. Stay away!

Good prof, he can sometimes get lost in thought but finds his way back to the point. He gives all of the exams questions before hand and is very clear with what he wants. He doesn't post anything online so make sure to show up in class and take notes. There is also summaries of readings that are graded and handed it at the final exam. Easy A.
Funny prof but lectures can be long and boring. He gives the exam questions in advance. Midterm, final and reading summaries.

Prof knows he's stuff. He can seem rude and talk a lot but is generally a good prof. PAY ATTENTION, and take organized notes to be able to write a lot on exams. He randomly gives out exams questions during lectures so attend classes. Do lectures and resumers as class goes. Watch the videos online. They are the best for exams. I recommend him.

Loved Gardaz.  He's funny, nice, cool, and just seems like an actual human.  Lectures were long, but he made them bearable. He is clear about what he wants from the first day of class.  If you have a good attitude and just do the work so you are ready for class, you'll do fine.  And you cannot NOT laugh with Gardaz!

Lectures are very scattered. He often went too slowly at the beginning and skipped material at the end bc he ran out of time. Midterm and exam were 3 essay questions that he gave ahead of time, this was helpful bc it allowed us to look up material that should have been covered in class but wasn't. Readings are long but necessary to pass.

TOUT EST PARFAIT. Le prof est stimulant et maintient éveillé! Aucun cours n'est posté sur le campus virtuel,il faut prendre des notes et assister à TOUS les cours. Il donne aussi les 3 questions d'examen au milieu du cours, donc restez attentifs. Tout est entrepris pour qu'on réussisse car il NOTE les lectures et donne les questions d'exam.
Très passionné de sa matière. Bon communicateur. Utilise powerpoint mais ne les mets pas online. Cours intéressant.

Pretty easy class, but you must attend since he doesnt put his slides online. He's very passionate about the subject, but is off subject often (because he's really into it). Very easy going and flexible.
Prof. Gardaz is one of the best.  He was professional and very interesting in the scientific study of religion.  He really knew his stuff.
Smart guy. Can be a jerk sometimes but he really knows what he's talking about. Funny guy also. All in all, a good class.
Gardaz knows his subject, and he's well-dressed (charming really) but he can once in a while be a big jerk.  Overall though, friendly and a good professor.
His lecture are incredibly dull which don't elaborate on the challenging texts we have to read.  He is not polite to Anglophone students even when it 's an English class....avoid him if you can!

Didn't like this class (SRS2522) at all. The lectures didn't add anything to the texts we had to read. Boring and useless documentaries every class. I wouldn't recommend this class if you already have read a bit on ancient religions, you won't learn anything new, really. Just grab any book on ancient religions and you'll learn more...

This class was reallly easy. Show up, listen, write good notes... exam is a sure thing. 3 essay type questions which globally refer to each religion covered. write as much as you can and you will be rewarded.
He's cute and knows his stuff. Though all the movies he played bugged me, he was a good prof.
Great Prof and great class! I would definitely recommend taking this class (though it is not optional for Religious Studies students ;) )

If you have the opporunity to take this course or ANY course with Professor Gardaz - do so!! It will be the best decision you make in your University career! Without question, Professor Gardaz is one of the most knowledgable Professor's at the University of Ottawa. A+++
